\q2 there’s no helper for them.
\q1
\v 14 They come \add quickly\add* like \add through\add* a wide breach \add in the wall\add*.
\q2 They have rolled themselves under the devastation.
\q1
\v 15 Terrors have been turned against me.
\q1 They persue my honour like the wind.
\q1 and my prosperity has disappeared like cloud.
\q1
\v 16 Now my life pours itself out within me.
\q1 Days of suffering have taken hold of me.
\q1
\v 17 Night pierces my bones from upon me,
\q1 and the pains that gnaw at me never rest.
\q1
\v 18 My clothing is transformed through great strength.
\q1 My garment ties me up by the collar.
\q1
\v 19 He throws me into the mud,
